description.narrative: During the period of January to December 2019, 819,167 children under the age of five years, pregnant and lactating mothers were reached with life-saving nutrition services including UNICEF Cross Border Nutrition Programme, including 550,000 pregnant and lactating mothers and 260,000 children under the age of five years across 460 high severity communities in 44 sub-districts in North-West Syria, including at least 2,000 disabled children. The newly introduced integrated Rapid Response Teams along with the regular fixed facility nutrition services have been made available in 32 out of 60 accessible sub-districts during 2019. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/04/2020
